                        <img class="H-MTGOX-image" src="../../assets/his_imgs/mtgox.jpg">
                            <p>
                                Mt.Gox was a bitcoin exchange platform, and by 2014 was the largest bitcoin intermediary by handling over 70% of all BTC (Bitcoin).
                                But behind the scene, this company was hiding a terrible secret: what as first impression seemed a great company,
                                indeed was just a disorganized and discordant organization, with poor security procedures and serious issues relating to the source code of the website itself.
                                Those problems lead to a massive hack of the system itself, that lead to a total loss of 745,000 Bitcoin (reached already 850,000 by now).
                                Even if the bankrupt of the company
                                was caused by this massive hack attack, the major blame is on the company itself and on its source code; because it was clear after the events
                                that there were too many flaws in the System, which leads to easy fraudulent withdrawals.
                                So the point is that this cannot be considered a properly hack attack, because everything was possible since the software had issues itself.
                              </p>
